footer: footer.title: {[Helvetica x 6]}{[7.97 x 6]}{[normal x 6]}{[null x 6]} //M: male; F: female; CN: central neurocytoma; DA: diffuse astrocytoma; GBM: glioblastoma; Germ: germinoma; ML: malignant lymphoma; Meta: metastasis; MS: multiple sclerosis; AA: anaplastic astrocytoma; Rt: right; Lt: left; Caud: caudate; Lat: lateral; T: trans; Vent: ventricular; Cort: cortical. Gross-total resection was defined as no evidence of residual enhancement, subtotal resection was defined as anything more than 5% residual tumor, and partial resection was defined as anything more than 50% residual tumor. We were able to collect sufficient specimens for pathological diagnosis in all 18 patients. In addition, all patients were assessed immediately after surgery and long term for any evidence of neurological deficits or other surgical complications.
